Christ, and of several other early saints.  See also  Philippa ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":4,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":29,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":42,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":51,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Philip De Clanvowe was born in 1286, in Herefordshire, England, his father, William ap Hywel, was 27 and his mother, Margaret Stanton, was 21. He married Philippa Talbot in 1311, in Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1347, in Hereford, Herefordshire, England, at the age of 61, and was buried in Yazor, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1286–1347":"1286–1347","1282–Male":"1282–Surnud","1303–Female":"1303–Surnud","1315–1372":"1315–1372","1260–1286":"1260–1286","1265–Female":"1265–Surnud","1286":"1286","Abt 1315":"umbes 1315","1372":"1372","1260":"1260","1282":"1282